examples.en: The wall collapsed
The business collapsed.
The girls collapsed into a fit of the giggles.
The roof collapsed.
The table collapsed under the weight of the food.
The stock market collapsed.
I was so exhausted when I got home, I just collapsed on the sofa.
The roof had collapsed long ago.
She came home from work and collapsed on the sofa.
Dozens of people were trapped in the rubble when the building collapsed.
They finally collapsed in a heap on the grass.
I bought some go-go stock and it collapsed immediately.
The roof, unable to sustain the weight of all the snow, collapsed.
He collapsed on stage during the performance and had to be rushed to the hospital.
The extensive warehouse collapsed and fell outwards with a terrific crash into the street.
The bench collapsed under the weight of (=unable to support the weight of) so many people.
Some roofs collapsed beneath the weight of (=unable to support the weight of) so much snow.
The roof of the old barn collapsed.
The luxury car market has collapsed.
Uncle Ted's chair collapsed under his weight.
She collapsed, senseless, after hitting her head.
We came in and collapsed thankfully onto our beds.
His wife called for an ambulance when he collapsed.
He collapsed with a heart attack while he was dancing.
The crying child ran to his mother and collapsed in her arms.
A wall collapsed and ten people were killed in the panic-stricken stampede.
